<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFFD6A42F7EF923718F4BC4D" pageId="6" pageNumber="764" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFFD6A42F7EF923718F4BC4D" blockId="6.[2066,2661,1055,1483]" lastBlockId="6.[1450,2666,1490,3459]" pageId="6" pageNumber="764">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFFD6A42F73F92371733BFBD" authorityName="Bowditch" authorityYear="1825" box="[2243,2355,1134,1167]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Nyctalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="764" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Nyctalus</taxonomicName>
seems to be nested well within Pipustrellus close to P. nathusuu, making 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFFD6A42F76C92E41720BFEC" authorityName="Kaup" authorityYear="1829" box="[2192,2336,1213,1246]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="764" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pipistrellus</taxonomicName>
paraphyletic, and indicating that further studies into the relationships between the two genera are greatly needed. N. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFFD6A42F6DD936A1781BE66" baseAuthorityName="Gerbe" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[2337,2433,1331,1364]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Nyctalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="764" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="plancyi">plancyi</taxonomicName>
seems to be the most basal lineage within the genus. The species has generally been included in N. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFFD6A42F7BE93F716A2BEF9" authorityName="Schreber" authorityYear="1774" box="[2114,2210,1454,1483]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Nyctalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="764" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="noctula">noctula</taxonomicName>
, which has led to some confusion over geographic limits, but this species is recognized here based on its genetic and morphological distinctions. Race velutinus has occasionally been treated as a distinct species. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFFD6A42F95C9078195BBD70" baseAuthorityName="Hodgson" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[1696,1883,1569,1602]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Nyctalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="764" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="plancyi" subSpecies="labiatus">Race labiatus</taxonomicName>
was previously considered a subspecies of N. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFFD6A42F5FB90781467BD70" authorityName="Schreber" authorityYear="1774" box="[2567,2663,1569,1602]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Nyctalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="764" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="noctula">noctula</taxonomicName>
but is morphologically very distinct from that species, according to unpublished data by G. Csorba and measurements from S. V. Kruskop and D. A. Vasenkov in 2016, which also compared them with N. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFFD6A42F7F490CE1668BD8A" baseAuthorityName="Gerbe" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[2056,2152,1687,1720]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Nyctalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="764" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="plancyi">plancyi</taxonomicName>
(based on a few samples). To date, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFFD6A42FA4C90E61861BDD2" baseAuthorityName="Hodgson" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[1456,1633,1727,1760]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Nyctalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="764" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="plancyi" subSpecies="labiatus">race labiatus</taxonomicName>
has not been compared genetically with N. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFFD6A42F70A90E61756BDD2" authorityName="Schreber" authorityYear="1774" box="[2294,2390,1727,1760]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Nyctalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="764" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="noctula">noctula</taxonomicName>
or N. p. plancy: in any published articles; for the present it is provisionally treated as a subspecies of N. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFFD6A42FA2A91571836BC1D" baseAuthorityName="Gerbe" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[1494,1590,1806,1839]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Nyctalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="764" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="plancyi">plancyi</taxonomicName>
, although it almost certainly represents a distinct species, as indicated by its morphological divergence. The species name is sometimes misspelled plancei. Three subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
